Population structure 2: \(G_{st}\) in the machine

Zhian N. Kamvar

September 30, 2014

  • Purpose
  • Required packages and data
  • Custom Function
  • \(G_{st}\) heatmaps by population
  • \(G_{st}\) heatmaps by population and year

Purpose

This document will explore pairwise \(G_{st}\) among populations. The funcion pairwise_Gst_Nei from the package mmod will be utilized for these calculations and a heatmap will be drawn.

To make sure that we arent making any comparisons with populations of sample size of 1, we are setting the minimum sample size to be 10.

Custom Function

heat_gst <- function(gst){
  gst.df <- melt(as.matrix(gst), value.name = "Gst")
  outPlot <- ggplot(gst.df, aes(x = factor(Var1), y = factor(Var2), fill = Gst)) +
    geom_tile() +
    theme_classic() +
    myTheme +
    scale_fill_gradient2(low = "blue", high = "yellow", mid = "black") +
    xlab("") +
    ylab("") +
    labs(fill = expression("G[st]")) +
    scale_y_discrete(expand = c(0, 0)) +
    scale_x_discrete(expand = c(0, 0))
  return(outPlot)
}

get_gst <- function(x) Gst_Nei(selPopSize(x, n = 10))

Gst_heatmap <- function(x){
  gst <- pairwise_Gst_Nei(selPopSize(x, n = 10))
  plot <- heat_gst(gst)
  return(plot)
}

\(G_{st}\) heatmaps by population and year

These heatmaps will be organized by population and year, but they are sorted by year. Lines will be placed demarking the year so that within year \(G_{st}\) can be compared.

get_gst(setpop(ramdat, ~ZONE2/Pop))
## $per.locus
##  PrMS6A1  Pr9C3A1 PrMS39A1 PrMS45A1 PrMS43A1 
## -0.01046 -0.01054  0.10016 -0.01938  0.14474 
## 
## $global
## [1] 0.05437
z2 <- Gst_heatmap(setpop(ramdat, ~ZONE2/Pop))
z2labs <- sub("^.+?_20", "20", unique(z2$data$Var1))
intercepts <- (which(!duplicated(z2labs)) - 0.5)[-1]

z2 + geom_vline(xintercept = intercepts, color = "white", size = 1.5) + 
  geom_hline(yintercept = intercepts, color = "white", size = 1.5)
